een coasts is consistently evident for individual environments (including freshwater, estuarine, and marine waters) and countries. While the focus of publications is unevenly distributed among research themes and taxa, the paucity of comparative analyses among countries is especially striking. Despite the general increment in research effort within the discipline, we consider there is an urgent need for more solid and concerted multinational efforts to address (financially, scientifically and socially) the conspicuous gaps in aquatic invasion research. Failing to make these efforts is probably the major threat hampering the development of successful long term programs and strategies directed to prevent, manage and/or control the introduction of exotic species and their many impacts in the continent.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Schwindt, Evangelina", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Bortolus, Alejandro", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Chapter 2", "Chapter 6", "biodiversity", "environment assessment", "IPBES", "Alien Invasive Species Assessment AIS", "invasive species"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/5ad750ff0eb263618a9b810dcdb9d78f", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/b9a8302f10a19741a528829bd0441a979bf4625dcb056022cf3e098d3b30f8cd", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/2352922/items/QFDFFAZU", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/2352922/items/QFDFFAZU", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/644d84c72af8e060d58f1a8536e8a924!/b82709-85225", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/359bd494433933b868f85e88d3437f76", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.1080/14634988.2017.1404413", "relation": "isVariantFormOf", "resource_type": "publication", "scheme": "doi"}, {"ident